<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-06-27T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-06-27T12:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/114: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-06-27T13:00:00-04:00">June
                                        27, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>271. [For Davis] Your 360, June 26, 5 p.m. We agree with the British
                                that it would be inadvisable to extend either the preliminary
                                conversations or the 1935 Conference beyond the five principal Naval
                                Powers.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>